# CODEOWNERS — auto-routes PR reviews by file path.
#
# Syntax: <pattern>  <@owner1> <@owner2> ...
#   - Patterns are gitignore-style globs (* matches a single path segment, ** matches any depth).
#   - The LAST matching line wins — general rules at the top, specific rules at the bottom.
#   - Owners can be @user, @org/team-name, or email addresses.
#
# Paired with branch protection → "Require review from Code Owners", the matched
# owner's approval becomes mandatory before merge.
# Repo admins can bypass when "Allow administrators to bypass" is enabled on the
# branch protection rule.

# Default owner — applies to the entire repo
*   @EdiWeeks
